WEBVTT

00:04.743 --> 00:07.137
<i>In the nation's</i> <i>
largest city,</i>

00:07.181 --> 00:09.879
<i>the vicious and violent</i> <i>
members of the underworld</i>

00:09.922 --> 00:11.489
<i>are hunted by the detectives</i>

00:11.533 --> 00:14.710
<i>of the Organized Crime</i> <i>
Control Bureau.</i>

00:14.753 --> 00:16.625
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:17.930 --> 00:19.845
Bet you anything that
Wheatley and McClane

00:19.889 --> 00:21.064
<i>are working together.</i>

00:21.108 --> 00:23.501
Elliot, don't.

00:23.545 --> 00:25.677
I just want to get McClane
back where he belongs.

00:25.721 --> 00:26.939
As do I, Governor.

00:26.983 --> 00:29.855
Every division
and every bureau is engaged.

00:29.899 --> 00:31.770
What are you thinkin'?

00:31.814 --> 00:33.424
You gotta be kidding me.

00:33.468 --> 00:35.078
It doesn't sit well with me,

00:35.122 --> 00:37.080
trying to convince you
to trust Richard.

00:37.124 --> 00:38.647
But you could do so much good.

00:38.690 --> 00:41.563
Oh, I did my best.
Now it's up to you.

00:41.606 --> 00:43.521
You're familiar
with Detective Elliot Stabler.

00:43.565 --> 00:46.307
If you ever come
near my family, I'll kill you.

00:46.350 --> 00:48.744
Are you telling me Stabler
is an overzealous cop?

00:48.787 --> 00:51.399
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:51.442 --> 00:54.445
[whispers]
I think I got eyes on them.

00:54.489 --> 00:55.794
[whispers]
I can't see anything.

01:00.451 --> 01:04.064
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:04.107 --> 01:05.543
So what's the FBI saying?

01:05.587 --> 01:08.416
Nothing, besides the power
being out for a few hours.

01:08.459 --> 01:09.765
We know that. We were there.

01:09.808 --> 01:11.549
My connection at the New York
office says that

01:11.593 --> 01:13.725
right before McClane got into
the wrong car last night,

01:13.769 --> 01:15.379
there was a strange break
in communications

01:15.423 --> 01:16.337
for about a minute.

01:16.380 --> 01:17.599
Comms went down?

01:17.642 --> 01:19.035
Or someone interfered
with them.

01:19.079 --> 01:20.950
Those communications
were intentionally broken.

01:20.993 --> 01:23.300
Power was cut
from outside of the building.

01:23.344 --> 01:25.085
It was an area-wide outage.

01:25.128 --> 01:27.391
North Jersey Electric and Power

01:27.435 --> 01:29.219
got it back up
at 5:17 this morning.

01:29.263 --> 01:30.960
If CSU's trying
to pick up footprints,

01:31.003 --> 01:33.397
unfortunately, this is
a working construction site.

01:33.441 --> 01:34.746
What about the helicopter?

01:34.790 --> 01:36.792
It flew through
and out of New York airspace.

01:36.835 --> 01:39.011
You didn't happen
to catch the tail number?

01:39.055 --> 01:40.665
both: No.

01:40.709 --> 01:42.667
Well, it didn't have
a flight plan filed.

01:42.711 --> 01:44.843
It didn't breach any airspace,
so all we know was that it was

01:44.887 --> 01:47.542
a blip, and then it--
yeah, it disappeared.

01:47.585 --> 01:48.891
Maldonado,
what is this building?

01:48.934 --> 01:50.197
Who owns it?

01:50.240 --> 01:52.503
Costwick Investment Corp.
Interesting part:

01:52.547 --> 01:55.245
office space leased
at 750 a square foot.

01:55.289 --> 01:56.768
All pre-sold,
and there's a waiting list.

01:56.812 --> 01:59.119
Yeah, dig into that.
There's something there.

01:59.162 --> 02:00.598
Might be something here.

02:00.642 --> 02:01.773
What are you talking about?

02:01.817 --> 02:02.731
The building.

02:04.080 --> 02:04.994
What building is that?

02:05.037 --> 02:08.693
<i>♪</i>

02:08.737 --> 02:10.521
In D.C.,
we call this facility

02:10.565 --> 02:12.828
"the beating heart of
the global financial universe."

02:12.871 --> 02:15.700
Officially,
it's the Quartext Data Center.

02:15.744 --> 02:17.615
300,000 square feet
of connectivity,

02:17.659 --> 02:20.444
surrounded on all sides
by layers of impenetrability.

02:20.488 --> 02:22.794
Great,
sounds like a secure facility.

02:22.838 --> 02:23.926
But can it be hacked?

02:23.969 --> 02:25.797
Data protection here
is next level.

02:25.841 --> 02:28.626
There's a reason it's the
backbone of the stock exchange.

02:28.670 --> 02:30.280
What about the power outage
last night?

02:30.324 --> 02:31.499
A brief anomaly.

02:31.542 --> 02:33.196
By design,
these servers don't go down.

02:33.240 --> 02:35.285
The backup grid
kicks in instantaneously.

02:35.329 --> 02:36.808
What about the IDS?

02:38.810 --> 02:40.725
Sorry,
the Intrusion Detection System.

02:40.769 --> 02:42.640
That takes
a little longer to reboot.

02:42.684 --> 02:44.990
Yes, well, that could create
the smallest of windows,

02:45.034 --> 02:46.209
in theory.

02:46.253 --> 02:47.819
How small,
in theory, exactly?

02:47.863 --> 02:50.082
A few minutes. No more.

02:50.126 --> 02:51.780
But electronic traders
can exploit

02:51.823 --> 02:53.782
even the most
infinitesimal of time gaps

02:53.825 --> 02:56.132
to their advantage.
We saw this in 2008.

02:56.176 --> 02:58.134
2008, you were what?

02:58.178 --> 02:59.483
10 years old?

02:59.527 --> 03:01.398
You don't
have to answer that.

03:01.442 --> 03:03.008
So if your agency doesn't
believe

03:03.052 --> 03:06.838
there was a data breach last
night, why are you guys here?

03:06.882 --> 03:08.405
It's routine, Sergeant.

03:09.537 --> 03:11.016
Now, if you'll excuse us...

03:11.060 --> 03:15.412
<i>♪</i>

03:15.456 --> 03:17.936
What are they hiding?

03:17.980 --> 03:19.938
I think they're hiding what
they don't yet know

03:19.982 --> 03:21.462
that they're hiding.

03:21.505 --> 03:23.638
I think we now know why
Wheatley picked this location.

03:23.681 --> 03:25.248
And why he picked McClane.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.904
Wheatley's like 50.

03:28.947 --> 03:30.819
Back in the day,
he did some cool stuff.

03:30.862 --> 03:32.647
But he is not
slick enough to exploit

03:32.690 --> 03:34.344
that brief window
that the IDS was down.

03:34.388 --> 03:36.041
McClane is.

03:36.085 --> 03:38.914
Wheatley needed McClane in
order to hack this data center,

03:38.957 --> 03:40.742
and what,
defraud the financial system?

03:42.265 --> 03:43.571
We talking billions?

03:45.268 --> 03:46.704
Trillions, actually.

03:46.748 --> 03:48.837
Assuming McClane was able
to take advantage

03:48.880 --> 03:51.753
of the 15-minute breach,
that is a distinct possibility.

03:51.796 --> 03:54.146
These guys are never gonna
acknowledge that possibility

03:54.190 --> 03:57.019
because they don't want to
create a panic in the markets.

03:57.062 --> 03:59.587
Imagine the panic
when it turns out to be true.

04:01.458 --> 04:04.853
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:04.896 --> 04:11.642
<i>♪</i>

04:49.506 --> 04:51.726
[doorbell rings]
Someone get that.

04:55.382 --> 04:57.471
Can someone get that?

05:05.305 --> 05:07.394
[doorbell rings]
You can't hear this?

05:15.663 --> 05:17.534
True friendship is like a--

05:19.275 --> 05:20.885
- Go on.
- Um...

05:20.929 --> 05:24.236
I was just--this is
for Bernadette.

05:24.280 --> 05:25.368
Huh.

05:27.327 --> 05:28.458
Oh, Bernadette...

05:29.894 --> 05:32.984
Is that Miles? What happened?
Did you scare him away?

05:33.028 --> 05:34.508
I didn't scare anybody.
Who's Miles?

05:34.551 --> 05:36.901
Mr. Darman? He lives in 3B.

05:36.945 --> 05:40.992
[chuckles]
Yeah, he's a friend of mine.

05:41.036 --> 05:42.124
Friend?

05:42.167 --> 05:43.255
He's a super nice guy.

05:43.299 --> 05:44.344
Used to be
a traveling salesman,

05:44.387 --> 05:46.041
but he's retired, so...

05:46.084 --> 05:47.825
he's got a lot of time
to visit Grandma.

05:47.869 --> 05:51.481
He's just a friendly,
gentlemanly neighbor

05:51.525 --> 05:53.309
who brings me flowers.
- Mm.

05:53.353 --> 05:54.484
I saw you
puffin' away out there.

05:54.528 --> 05:55.877
How many is that today?

05:55.920 --> 05:58.358
I was just finishing
the one from this morning.

05:58.401 --> 06:00.490
I limit myself to three a day.

06:05.408 --> 06:08.237
Don't worry.
I won't bust you.

06:08.280 --> 06:11.849
Yeah, you better not.

06:16.898 --> 06:18.813
We wanna leave
this meeting intact.

06:18.856 --> 06:20.510
I got you.

06:20.554 --> 06:22.077
I'll follow your lead.

06:24.079 --> 06:28.562
Sergeant Bell, Detective
Stabler, what happened?

06:28.605 --> 06:30.172
From what we were able
to ascertain

06:30.215 --> 06:31.434
and from what we believe,

06:31.478 --> 06:34.045
it was either
a well-orchestrated escape,

06:34.089 --> 06:36.047
or McClane was abducted.

06:36.091 --> 06:38.049
On the 7th floor.

06:38.093 --> 06:39.399
What did you find?

06:39.442 --> 06:41.662
Richard Wheatley.

06:41.705 --> 06:44.491
Wait a minute.
You saw Wheatley?

06:44.534 --> 06:46.449
Yes, sir,
and Sebastian McClane.

06:46.493 --> 06:47.711
Why didn't you arrest them?

06:47.755 --> 06:49.234
There was a power outage,
sir,

06:49.278 --> 06:51.759
and by the time Sergeant Bell
and I got our bearings,

06:51.802 --> 06:54.326
the only thing to see was
a helicopter lifting off

06:54.370 --> 06:55.937
and flying away from the roof.

06:55.980 --> 06:57.852
Sergeant Bell,
can you corroborate

06:57.895 --> 06:59.897
what Detective Stabler
just reported?

06:59.941 --> 07:02.726
The power was cut,
and we heard a helicopter

07:02.770 --> 07:05.512
fly from the roof,
with who we assumed were

07:05.555 --> 07:07.035
McClane and Wheatley.

07:07.078 --> 07:09.037
You weren't asked what you
heard or what you assumed.

07:09.080 --> 07:10.865
Did you see Wheatley
in that building,

07:10.908 --> 07:12.519
or McClane, for that matter?

07:20.004 --> 07:22.093
No.

07:22.137 --> 07:23.530
I saw neither.

07:23.573 --> 07:25.096
But you did see
a helicopter fly overhead.

07:25.140 --> 07:26.489
Gentleman,
with all due respect,

07:26.533 --> 07:28.099
what I'm telling you are facts.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.798
McClane and Wheatley
were in that building,

07:30.841 --> 07:33.496
and they were there to hack
the Quartext Data Center.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.585
Detective,
Everett Willis, SEC.

07:35.629 --> 07:37.369
That facility
is designed to withstand

07:37.413 --> 07:38.762
almost any kind of attack.

07:38.806 --> 07:40.111
No damage was done.

07:40.155 --> 07:43.114
That power outage
was either a dry run,

07:43.158 --> 07:44.594
or they're already in.

07:44.638 --> 07:46.117
Now, let's be honest.
Nobody in this room

07:46.161 --> 07:47.510
wants to admit
that trusting Richard Wheatley

07:47.554 --> 07:48.946
was a bad idea.

07:48.990 --> 07:51.514
So Detective,
you're suggesting that Wheatley

07:51.558 --> 07:53.734
is behind what, exactly?

07:53.777 --> 07:56.301
Richard Wheatley
is behind the prison break

07:56.345 --> 08:00.131
of Sebastian McClane,
his escape from the FBI,

08:00.175 --> 08:03.178
and last night's attack
on their facility.

08:03.221 --> 08:05.528
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

08:05.572 --> 08:06.529
Sir.

08:06.573 --> 08:10.141
<i>♪</i>

08:10.185 --> 08:12.535
The last time anyone--
anyone being the two of you--

08:12.579 --> 08:14.711
saw McClane and Wheatley, was
right before the power outage.

08:14.755 --> 08:16.191
Well, McClane, anyway.

08:17.671 --> 08:18.976
Sorry,
but it's my understanding that

08:19.020 --> 08:21.718
Sergeant Bell didn't see--
- Let it go, Vicky.

08:21.762 --> 08:23.807
We're just running
hypothetical scenarios.

08:23.851 --> 08:26.810
Right, so a power outage
can cause fluctuations

08:26.854 --> 08:28.986
in the
Intrusion Detection System--

08:29.030 --> 08:31.119
Standard issue recipe
for a fatal security breach.

08:31.162 --> 08:32.424
Oh, you're back.

08:32.468 --> 08:34.818
It was a misunderstanding.
We cleared it up.

08:34.862 --> 08:36.516
- Mm.
- Visually, the manhunt

08:36.559 --> 08:38.343
is for McClane.

08:38.387 --> 08:40.998
We had him, the FBI lost him.

08:41.042 --> 08:43.914
Our best lead is Wheatley.
Wheatley is a ghost.

08:43.958 --> 08:45.437
One of the few things
we do know

08:45.481 --> 08:47.483
is that McClane has been
to Angela Wheatley's apartment.

08:47.527 --> 08:49.572
Where are we with getting
the warrant to surveil her?

08:49.616 --> 08:51.748
I'm leaning
on Frazier's office.

08:51.792 --> 08:53.402
But McClane is federal.

08:53.445 --> 08:57.145
So Anne is gonna have to make
it happen outside the purview

08:57.188 --> 08:58.276
of the U.S. Attorney.

08:58.320 --> 08:59.800
Yeah,
assuming we get the warrant.

09:01.410 --> 09:04.587
There's an empty apartment
above Angela Wheatley's.

09:04.631 --> 09:07.372
Cho, Maldonado,
you're newlyweds.

09:07.416 --> 09:08.678
You just moved in.

09:08.722 --> 09:10.071
Copy that, Sarge.

09:10.114 --> 09:11.463
Oh, awesome.

09:11.507 --> 09:13.030
You guys are, like,
kickin' it old school, huh?

09:13.074 --> 09:14.858
I'll install the
surveillance tools you need

09:14.902 --> 09:16.556
and teach you
how to operate them.

09:16.599 --> 09:18.035
They'll be next-gen,

09:18.079 --> 09:21.386
which should be simple enough
for a noob to handle.

09:21.430 --> 09:24.302
Are you sure you don't want
some seaweed salad?

09:24.346 --> 09:26.870
Yeah, no thanks.
Not my food group.

09:28.959 --> 09:31.048
Hold up, I think that's them.

09:31.092 --> 09:33.747
<i>Daniel recommended</i> <i>
the torchon de foie gras</i>

09:33.790 --> 09:36.053
<i>instead of the bollito misto.</i>

09:36.097 --> 09:37.446
Hope you like.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.056
<i>[tense music]</i>

09:39.100 --> 09:42.233
And, uh,
what are we celebrating?

09:42.277 --> 09:45.846
Ah,
what are we not celebrating?

09:45.889 --> 09:48.413
Mm. You smell delicious.

09:48.457 --> 09:49.763
Are you getting this, Sarge?

09:49.806 --> 09:52.113
Yep, yep.
We're right here with you.

09:52.156 --> 09:53.984
[cork explodes]
- Whoo!

09:54.028 --> 09:55.290
<i>[laughs]</i>

09:55.333 --> 09:57.684
<i>I'll never get tired</i> <i>
of that sound.</i>

09:57.727 --> 10:00.774
Wait for it.
[glass clinking]

10:00.817 --> 10:01.775
White truffles.

10:01.818 --> 10:03.907
[gasps] My favorite.

10:03.951 --> 10:09.304
And diamond bracelets
for days.

10:10.697 --> 10:12.263
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

10:12.307 --> 10:15.092
Yes, a little token
for your job interview.

10:15.136 --> 10:17.747
Oh, my God.
[both chuckle]

10:17.791 --> 10:18.966
Isn't that something?

10:19.009 --> 10:23.013
Not enough for you, my love.

10:23.057 --> 10:25.407
I'm gonna buy you the world

10:25.450 --> 10:27.365
because you deserve the world.

10:30.064 --> 10:33.284
I really hope that I don't
blow this interview tomorrow.

10:33.328 --> 10:34.938
<i>I really wanna go back</i> <i>
to teaching.</i>

10:34.982 --> 10:36.592
Can you see
inside the apartment?

10:36.636 --> 10:40.422
He can if my tech is working
the way I designed it to work.

10:40.465 --> 10:42.511
<i>You're going to be stunning.</i>
[buttons beeping]

10:42.554 --> 10:44.948
<i>You are stunning. Here.</i>

10:44.992 --> 10:47.734
Some truffles, new.

10:47.777 --> 10:49.170
- Okay.
- Yes.

10:49.213 --> 10:52.390
- Oh! Okay.
- Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

10:52.434 --> 10:53.653
- Mm-hmm.
- You ready?

10:53.696 --> 10:54.697
- Mm-hmm.
- You're not ready.

10:54.741 --> 10:57.134
- [giggles]
- Ah.

10:58.222 --> 11:01.095
<i>Mmm.</i> <i>
We are celebrating</i>

11:01.138 --> 11:05.273
the renewal of our bounty.

11:06.491 --> 11:08.363
Renewal of bounty?
Wait, what's that?

11:08.406 --> 11:10.321
Is that some kind
of new app he's developing?

11:10.365 --> 11:12.672
He's alluding
to getting rich again.

11:12.715 --> 11:19.156
<i>♪</i>

11:19.200 --> 11:21.158
[whispers]
And what a bounty it is.

11:21.202 --> 11:22.377
Mm.

11:24.161 --> 11:28.122
<i>[heavy breathing]</i> <i>
Richard.</i>

11:28.165 --> 11:29.863
The renewal of our bounty?

11:29.906 --> 11:32.735
Mm.
The renewal of our bounty.

11:32.779 --> 11:35.346
Has never been a thing.

11:35.390 --> 11:36.521
Not a thing.

11:36.565 --> 11:40.003
<i>♪</i>

11:40.047 --> 11:41.396
Is there someone else?

11:44.529 --> 11:46.009
Don't tell me you're getting it
on with that

11:46.053 --> 11:48.446
scrawny, escaped felon.

11:48.490 --> 11:51.014
What are you talking about?

11:51.058 --> 11:51.841
Oh, God.

11:51.885 --> 11:52.842
- Eat it.
- No.

11:52.886 --> 11:54.235
[whispers]
Eat it.

11:54.278 --> 11:55.453
No.

11:57.542 --> 12:00.154
You know what?

12:00.197 --> 12:05.594
I don't care who it is.
It stops now.

12:05.637 --> 12:06.726
Right now.

12:09.772 --> 12:14.821
The idea of you
with another man...

12:16.561 --> 12:21.784
I can't tolerate it.

12:21.828 --> 12:26.180
Do you hear me?
I can't tolerate it.

12:26.223 --> 12:27.355
Mm-hmm.

12:29.618 --> 12:30.750
Don't.

12:31.838 --> 12:32.839
Okay.

12:32.882 --> 12:36.886
Don't make me do something

12:36.930 --> 12:40.716
that we'll
both regret, my love.

12:40.760 --> 12:41.761
<i>He has a knife</i> <i>
to her throat.</i>

12:41.804 --> 12:42.892
<i>Should we go in?</i>

12:42.936 --> 12:45.460
No, he's not gonna hurt her.

12:45.503 --> 12:47.723
<i>Right. Okay.</i>

12:47.767 --> 12:49.246
<i>Okay.</i>

12:49.290 --> 12:51.292
We got him
right where we want him.

12:55.731 --> 12:57.689
<i>All of the big guys</i> <i>
are in the tank,</i>

12:57.733 --> 12:59.169
<i>and on the brink of collapse.</i>

12:59.213 --> 13:00.605
<i>Even Apple, Boeing--</i>

13:00.649 --> 13:02.259
How far out front are we?

13:02.303 --> 13:04.609
Exactly seven milliseconds
ahead of the market.

13:04.653 --> 13:05.741
And that's enough?

13:05.785 --> 13:06.873
It's a lifetime.

13:08.657 --> 13:10.354
Then let's get buying.

13:10.398 --> 13:12.487
Buying, selling,
and shorting.

13:12.530 --> 13:13.836
I see an order
from a big player,

13:13.880 --> 13:15.577
and jump in before
Wall Street has time to react.

13:15.620 --> 13:17.013
Genius.

13:17.057 --> 13:19.450
High frequency trading
at warp speed.

13:19.494 --> 13:21.235
[keyboard clicking]

13:21.278 --> 13:22.323
I've never said this before,

13:22.366 --> 13:26.675
but I wish
I'd designed that code.

13:26.718 --> 13:29.025
I'm also
artificially inflating a stock.

13:29.069 --> 13:30.287
CrowdBlitz.

13:30.331 --> 13:32.550
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:32.594 --> 13:34.552
- Like GameStop?
- Exactly.

13:34.596 --> 13:37.468
I've driven it up more than
10,000 times its actual value.

13:37.512 --> 13:39.122
Hmm.

13:39.166 --> 13:42.691
Those symbols--the ones at the
end of every transaction,

13:42.734 --> 13:43.823
what are they?

13:43.866 --> 13:45.999
Random code.
It's nothing.

13:46.042 --> 13:47.261
You'd be bored
if I explained it.

13:47.304 --> 13:49.306
I've never seen anything
like that before.

13:49.350 --> 13:51.265
You're welcome.

13:51.308 --> 13:53.093
And you're rich.

13:53.136 --> 13:55.573
I'm gonna get back everything
those filthy animals

13:55.617 --> 13:58.141
took from me and more.

13:58.185 --> 14:00.665
You see, my friend,
this isn't just about money.

14:00.709 --> 14:02.319
It's about respect,

14:02.363 --> 14:05.757
and you--you are richer
than you've ever been.

14:05.801 --> 14:11.328
<i>♪</i>

14:11.372 --> 14:14.810
Except unlike you, I have no
intention of keeping a penny.

14:14.854 --> 14:16.246
And I'm not your friend.

14:21.773 --> 14:23.166
[doorbell rings]

14:31.871 --> 14:33.916
"It's the time
you spent with your rose

14:33.960 --> 14:36.397
that makes your rose
so important."

14:36.440 --> 14:37.789
Antoine de Saint-Exupéry.

14:37.833 --> 14:40.444
I love that one.

14:40.488 --> 14:44.884
Would, um, you like to have
some coffee and a croissant?

14:44.927 --> 14:47.147
Miles, come on in.
Have some coffee.

14:47.190 --> 14:48.278
[stammers]

14:48.322 --> 14:49.714
My mother,
she always makes enough

14:49.758 --> 14:51.020
for the entire neighborhood.

14:51.064 --> 14:53.762
Here, Miles. Sit over there.

14:56.025 --> 14:57.548
We don't
usually have croissants.

14:57.592 --> 14:58.898
[chuckles]

14:58.941 --> 15:02.466
Miles just moved here
two months ago.

15:02.510 --> 15:03.467
Where are you from?

15:03.511 --> 15:05.600
Uh, Cliffside Park.

15:05.643 --> 15:06.993
Jersey.
- Home of the famed mobster,

15:07.036 --> 15:08.908
Willie Moretti.
Do you know him?

15:10.605 --> 15:12.389
- Definitely not.
- [laughs]

15:12.433 --> 15:14.826
I'm not connected
in any way to Mr. Moretti.

15:14.870 --> 15:18.395
Yeah, that was a joke.
He's always teasing.

15:18.439 --> 15:19.614
You're such a jerk.

15:19.657 --> 15:20.963
[laughs]

15:21.007 --> 15:22.660
I love you, too.
Miles, nice meeting you.

15:22.704 --> 15:23.966
I'm off to work, Mama.

15:24.010 --> 15:26.012
Bernadette tells me
you're a police officer.

15:26.055 --> 15:27.317
True!

15:27.361 --> 15:29.319
So if you get fresh with her,
I'll arrest you.

15:29.363 --> 15:32.279
[coughs]
Thank you.

15:36.805 --> 15:38.067
So it sounds like
Angela's gonna be

15:38.111 --> 15:39.939
out of her apartment tomorrow.

15:39.982 --> 15:40.983
She's interviewing
for a position

15:41.027 --> 15:42.376
at Colby Girl School.

15:42.419 --> 15:45.988
The warrant allows us
to surveil her snail mail.

15:46.032 --> 15:47.947
Do me a favor when she's out.

15:47.990 --> 15:49.078
Get into her apartment

15:49.122 --> 15:51.211
and grab some
of her underwear for me.

15:51.254 --> 15:53.213
I can't do that,
Detective Stabler.

15:53.256 --> 15:55.519
It violates the terms
of the warrant.

15:55.563 --> 15:56.694
I'm sorry.

15:58.522 --> 16:00.437
Everything okay?

16:00.481 --> 16:03.788
Yeah, I just asked
Detective Cho to, uh,

16:03.832 --> 16:05.094
do something questionable,

16:05.138 --> 16:07.923
and she was fully
within her rights to refuse.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.446
Thanks, Detective.

16:09.490 --> 16:10.447
Okay.

16:10.491 --> 16:13.581
<i>♪</i>

16:13.624 --> 16:16.584
Maybe you should rethink
what you're asking her to do.

16:16.627 --> 16:18.978
You look good.
Where you going?

16:19.021 --> 16:21.458
Lunch date with Denise.
It's our anniversary.

16:21.502 --> 16:22.677
Congratulations.

16:25.941 --> 16:28.770
Don't worry.
Got you on the panties.

16:28.813 --> 16:30.859
[laughs]

16:30.902 --> 16:32.774
Pink, ideally.

16:43.045 --> 16:45.482
Happy anniversary.

16:45.526 --> 16:47.876
Ayanna.

16:47.919 --> 16:49.965
I don't believe
you've met my new top aide.

16:50.009 --> 16:52.446
Carmen Riley, Ayanna Bell.

16:52.489 --> 16:55.318
Don't worry, Carmen
is discreet and trustworthy.

16:55.362 --> 16:56.667
Nice to meet you.

16:56.711 --> 16:58.669
Likewise.

16:58.713 --> 17:01.107
Is there a reason we need
to be discreet and trustworthy?

17:01.150 --> 17:02.847
Apologies, Sergeant Bell.

17:02.891 --> 17:05.763
Your wife kindly allowed us to
co-opt your anniversary lunch

17:05.807 --> 17:08.462
for a few moments.
We'll be gone soon.

17:08.505 --> 17:09.724
Where is my wife?

17:09.767 --> 17:10.899
Oh, she didn't want
to be here for this.

17:10.942 --> 17:13.293
She's hanging back
until we're finished.

17:13.336 --> 17:14.946
Please, sit.

17:14.990 --> 17:18.254
<i>[low tense music]</i>

17:18.298 --> 17:24.913
<i>♪</i>

17:24.956 --> 17:26.697
We want to talk to you
about Detective Stabler.

17:26.741 --> 17:27.959
What about him?

17:28.003 --> 17:31.311
His obsession
with Richard Wheatley.

17:31.354 --> 17:34.009
Ayanna, the governor
and I ran into one another

17:34.053 --> 17:35.793
at a reception
the other evening.

17:35.837 --> 17:37.056
And he told me
about how troubled he was

17:37.099 --> 17:38.187
by the things
he's been hearing.

17:38.231 --> 17:40.276
If Stabler's
obsessed with anything,

17:40.320 --> 17:41.973
it's with
averting a catastrophe

17:42.017 --> 17:43.366
in the stock market.

17:43.410 --> 17:45.107
There are fluctuations
in the market all the time.

17:45.151 --> 17:47.457
This one doesn't yet approach
the level of catastrophe.

17:47.501 --> 17:49.155
Your task force was charged

17:49.198 --> 17:51.505
with tracking down
an escaped convict.

17:51.548 --> 17:55.117
And somehow, Detective
Stabler has conflated it

17:55.161 --> 17:59.252
with his spiraling vendetta
against his nemesis.

17:59.295 --> 18:00.557
[sighs]

18:00.601 --> 18:07.521
<i>♪</i>

18:08.913 --> 18:10.219
That was a damn ambush.

18:10.263 --> 18:11.916
I would've given
you a heads-up.

18:11.960 --> 18:13.048
I didn't know
what that meeting was about.

18:13.092 --> 18:14.093
What were you
even doing there?

18:14.136 --> 18:15.529
I swear, I don't know.

18:15.572 --> 18:18.401
Kilbride's been including me
in more and more things.

18:18.445 --> 18:20.229
He knows you're a plant.
I'm pulling you out.

18:20.273 --> 18:21.665
Aw, no way
he suspects I'm a cop.

18:21.709 --> 18:23.058
I'm confident he trusts me.

18:23.102 --> 18:26.409
It is not your job
to make that determination.

18:26.453 --> 18:27.410
It's mine.

18:29.369 --> 18:30.805
And what he and Garcia
were saying?

18:32.981 --> 18:34.504
Just be careful.
- Of?

18:37.159 --> 18:38.769
What, you think
they're right about Stabler?

18:38.813 --> 18:40.989
I believe he's an honest cop.

18:41.032 --> 18:42.904
But I know how he roll
when he was undercover.

18:42.947 --> 18:44.645
I was there.

18:44.688 --> 18:47.387
No matter how good a cop he is,
that's in his DNA now.

18:47.430 --> 18:53.044
<i>♪</i>

18:56.744 --> 18:58.398
So where are we now?

18:58.441 --> 19:00.313
Last I looked,
the DOW was down 31%.

19:00.356 --> 19:02.663
Almost the biggest drop
in U.S. history.

19:02.706 --> 19:04.795
The market is in chaos.

19:04.839 --> 19:06.536
Things are up, down,
and all kinds of sideways.

19:06.580 --> 19:08.059
So how do we stop it?

19:08.103 --> 19:09.235
Arrest Richard Wheatley,

19:09.278 --> 19:11.193
and perp walk his ass
down Wall Street.

19:11.237 --> 19:13.804
I meant
how do we really stop it?

19:13.848 --> 19:15.850
We get inside
the Quartext servers,

19:15.893 --> 19:18.722
and you find the proof that
Wheatley hacked them.

19:18.766 --> 19:20.159
We need a rainbow table.

19:20.202 --> 19:22.378
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

19:22.422 --> 19:24.598
- Nice.
- What is that?

19:24.641 --> 19:26.687
Okay, uh, let's say
I'm trying to figure out

19:26.730 --> 19:29.690
your password to steal
all your personal information.

19:29.733 --> 19:32.040
To be clear,
he doesn't do that anymore.

19:32.083 --> 19:35.478
Okay, but if I were,
I would collect all

19:35.522 --> 19:36.827
the information
I could find on you.

19:36.871 --> 19:38.481
Your birthdate, favorite color,

19:38.525 --> 19:40.135
pet's name,
street you lived on.

19:40.179 --> 19:41.789
I'd look at all of that

19:41.832 --> 19:44.487
and see if there was
any kind of pattern.

19:44.531 --> 19:46.707
That collection of data
is a rainbow table.

19:46.750 --> 19:49.231
So if we're assuming Wheatley
embedded his own malware

19:49.275 --> 19:50.319
into the stock exchange servers--

19:50.363 --> 19:51.755
- And we are.
- Then the key

19:51.799 --> 19:53.888
to finding that malware
and cracking the code

19:53.931 --> 19:56.325
is likely in Wheatley's
personal information.

19:56.369 --> 19:57.544
Stabler and I
will give you access

19:57.587 --> 19:59.198
to all
of Wheatley's information

19:59.241 --> 20:01.548
from all of our investigations.

20:01.591 --> 20:03.854
Use all your resources
to do a deep dive.

20:03.898 --> 20:05.508
Let's go to work.
- Got a minute?

20:05.552 --> 20:06.988
Not right now.
On my way downtown

20:07.031 --> 20:08.076
to go to a meeting.

20:12.994 --> 20:14.996
Ange?

20:15.039 --> 20:18.042
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:18.086 --> 20:19.043
Ange.

20:19.087 --> 20:25.354
<i>♪</i>

20:25.398 --> 20:26.573
[laptop dings]

20:38.324 --> 20:42.066
[keyboard clicking]

20:42.110 --> 20:46.288
How many times have I told you
not to recycle old passwords?

20:46.332 --> 20:49.030
Looks like he just hacked
into her computer.

21:15.361 --> 21:16.579
[door clicks open]

21:18.233 --> 21:23.238
[chuckles]
Richard, this has got to stop.

21:23.282 --> 21:25.109
Never.

21:25.153 --> 21:27.808
I got you a suit for your
interview tomorrow at Colby.

21:29.549 --> 21:31.333
<i>You're gonna kill it, my love.</i>

21:31.377 --> 21:34.075
And I want you looking fire.

21:34.118 --> 21:35.468
Or murdering.

21:41.474 --> 21:42.953
If I get this job...

21:44.651 --> 21:47.001
We can have
a proper celebration.

21:48.655 --> 21:50.134
Looking forward.

21:50.178 --> 21:57.141
<i>♪</i>

21:57.185 --> 21:58.839
[sighs]

21:58.882 --> 22:00.319
What are you doing?

22:00.362 --> 22:02.451
Letting Jet know to retrieve
the selfie of Stabler

22:02.495 --> 22:04.584
before Mrs. Wheatley sees it.

22:04.627 --> 22:05.846
Professor.

22:05.889 --> 22:06.890
Sorry?

22:06.934 --> 22:09.284
Her name
is Professor Wheatley.

22:09.328 --> 22:10.981
And if you do that,
she has no way of knowing

22:11.025 --> 22:13.157
that her ex-husband
is in a jealous rage.

22:13.201 --> 22:15.377
I'm pretty sure
we don't want her to know that.

22:15.421 --> 22:17.336
We're putting her in danger.

22:17.379 --> 22:20.556
Don't worry.
Stabler knows what he's doing.

22:20.600 --> 22:27.694
<i>♪</i>

22:47.409 --> 22:48.367
May I take your coat?

22:48.410 --> 22:50.673
Ah, yes.

23:02.772 --> 23:05.209
What is all of this?

23:05.253 --> 23:07.255
I thought I'd pretend
to be in love with you.

23:13.261 --> 23:15.219
Why?

23:15.263 --> 23:17.396
[chuckles]

23:17.439 --> 23:19.659
It's good you're suspicious.

23:19.702 --> 23:21.269
It's what keeps us alive.

23:24.490 --> 23:28.537
To the truth

23:28.581 --> 23:31.279
in all its ugliness and beauty.

23:31.322 --> 23:32.280
[glasses clink]

23:35.631 --> 23:38.417
Please tell me what this is.

23:38.460 --> 23:39.940
What it is you want.

23:42.551 --> 23:44.597
Neither of us
is to be trusted.

23:46.729 --> 23:48.470
Let's just know and admit that.

23:48.514 --> 23:49.776
Why do you say that?

23:49.819 --> 23:51.255
Because we both know
it's true.

23:53.127 --> 23:55.608
I don't know
exactly when it changed...

23:57.218 --> 24:01.701
But whichever side
each of us is on,

24:01.744 --> 24:03.616
it's not the same one.

24:05.966 --> 24:08.577
- I am not back with Richard.
- I don't care.

24:08.621 --> 24:15.758
<i>♪</i>

24:17.760 --> 24:20.981
Because whatever you say to me,
I'm going to assume is a lie.

24:24.158 --> 24:26.508
[whispers] And you should
assume the same thing about me.

24:26.552 --> 24:32.296
<i>♪</i>

24:32.340 --> 24:33.297
Well.

24:34.908 --> 24:38.259
That's a vexing conundrum.

24:38.302 --> 24:42.350
If everything
either one of us says is a lie,

24:42.393 --> 24:44.265
then how do I know
when you're being true?

24:44.308 --> 24:45.832
You don't.

24:45.875 --> 24:47.311
Except for this.

24:49.879 --> 24:52.795
[whispers]
I don't know what you're doing.

24:52.839 --> 24:55.058
I don't know what game
you think you're playing.

24:57.017 --> 24:58.932
But please be careful.

25:01.848 --> 25:04.198
You're swimming
in very dangerous waters.

25:07.897 --> 25:10.334
That is so sweet of you
to be concerned for me.

25:10.378 --> 25:17.037
<i>♪</i>

25:19.605 --> 25:21.824
I'm gonna go freshen up.

25:21.868 --> 25:23.783
I'll be back in a bit.

25:32.574 --> 25:34.184
You're lying to me again.

25:34.228 --> 25:41.148
<i>♪</i>

25:47.110 --> 25:48.721
Headmaster's office?

25:48.764 --> 25:51.071
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:51.114 --> 25:58.078
<i>♪</i>

25:58.121 --> 26:01.342
[indistinct chatter]

26:01.385 --> 26:04.345
Richard.
What are you doing here?

26:04.388 --> 26:07.566
It's just like "The Prime
of Miss Jean Brodie."

26:07.609 --> 26:11.221
[as Miss Brodie] My girls
are the crème de la crme.

26:13.397 --> 26:14.355
[normal voice]
She was a bit of a libertine,

26:14.398 --> 26:15.486
wasn't she, Miss Brodie?

26:15.530 --> 26:18.098
Very much like my wife here.

26:18.141 --> 26:19.360
I am so sorry.

26:19.403 --> 26:21.667
I'm so incredibly sorry.

26:21.710 --> 26:22.798
I think my ex-husband

26:22.842 --> 26:26.149
is having one of his
psychotic breaks.

26:26.193 --> 26:27.542
If you'll excuse me--

26:27.586 --> 26:28.978
I'm surprised
that she wanted to teach

26:29.022 --> 26:31.590
at an all-girls school,
given her irrepressible lust

26:31.633 --> 26:33.722
for the muscular male physique.

26:35.202 --> 26:36.682
- [whispers] Damn you.
- I had to.

26:36.725 --> 26:39.119
Impressionable young minds
are at stake.

26:40.381 --> 26:42.905
I'm getting a lot of heat
from upstairs.

26:42.949 --> 26:44.211
How high up?

26:44.254 --> 26:47.083
Let's just say
Garcia has weighed in.

26:47.127 --> 26:48.650
Wheatley has
something on him.

26:48.694 --> 26:51.479
I'm no fan of his.
You know that.

26:51.522 --> 26:54.221
He wants me to psych Stabler.

26:54.264 --> 26:56.527
That means taking away
his gun and badge.

26:56.571 --> 26:58.617
That's what I'm gonna have
to do if he doesn't back down.

27:00.009 --> 27:03.317
I promise I will handle him.

27:03.360 --> 27:10.411
<i>♪</i>

27:11.760 --> 27:13.762
Again, what were you doing
with Stabler?

27:13.806 --> 27:15.068
Hmm?

27:15.111 --> 27:16.983
What were you doing?

27:17.026 --> 27:18.593
Oh, dear.

27:18.637 --> 27:19.725
You tripped.

27:19.768 --> 27:21.988
What the hell's
the matter with you?

27:22.031 --> 27:24.381
Do not put your hands on her!

27:24.425 --> 27:26.427
You understand me?

27:26.470 --> 27:28.734
No man touches my wife!

27:28.777 --> 27:34.783
<i>♪</i>

27:34.827 --> 27:35.828
Oh.

27:48.318 --> 27:50.146
Are you sleeping with him?

27:53.541 --> 27:55.586
It's none of your business.

27:59.503 --> 28:01.767
I'm gonna ask you
one last time,

28:01.810 --> 28:03.769
and you better
tell me the truth.

28:05.988 --> 28:10.471
Are you having sex
with Detective Stabler?

28:10.514 --> 28:14.170
I'm not having sex with him.

28:19.262 --> 28:21.221
He asked to see me,

28:21.264 --> 28:22.701
and he told me...

28:26.356 --> 28:29.403
He tried to tell me
I was in danger from you,

28:29.446 --> 28:32.319
and that
he was gonna protect me.

28:32.362 --> 28:35.104
[scoffs]
That's absurd.

28:35.148 --> 28:36.671
I know it is.

28:42.024 --> 28:44.461
I would never hurt you, baby.

28:46.637 --> 28:47.595
Ever.

28:50.293 --> 28:52.905
[sighs]
You see, McClane,

28:52.948 --> 28:56.735
I love her, and I need her.

28:58.214 --> 29:02.741
Everything we did, you and me,

29:02.784 --> 29:05.352
I did for her.

29:05.395 --> 29:09.008
Go ahead. Tell her what we did.

29:09.051 --> 29:10.618
Rot in hell.

29:10.661 --> 29:12.011
[laughs]

29:12.054 --> 29:13.795
Don't be an idiot.

29:13.839 --> 29:15.797
You know you can't
just walk out of here.

29:15.841 --> 29:16.842
You got what you wanted,

29:16.885 --> 29:18.452
and I definitely
got what I wanted.

29:18.495 --> 29:20.715
Then kill me!

29:20.759 --> 29:21.847
Come on.

29:21.890 --> 29:23.674
Kill me.

29:23.718 --> 29:25.938
No!

29:25.981 --> 29:29.463
What did you get, Sebastian?

29:29.506 --> 29:31.204
Richard said
you got what you wanted.

29:31.247 --> 29:33.597
He got millions of dollars,

29:33.641 --> 29:36.731
which for unknown reason,
he gave away to a bunch of NGOs

29:36.775 --> 29:39.168
and other
miscellaneous vagrants.

29:39.212 --> 29:43.999
<i>♪</i>

29:44.043 --> 29:45.740
You're an exceptional person.

29:51.137 --> 29:56.229
And, uh, if he got millions,
I can only imagine

29:56.272 --> 29:57.926
you got billions.

29:57.970 --> 30:00.407
- Not yet.
- Mm.

30:00.450 --> 30:04.019
But I am poised to.
[laughs]

30:04.063 --> 30:07.327
So you're gonna have
to figure out how to hide it,

30:07.370 --> 30:12.593
and, uh,
I am really good at that.

30:12.636 --> 30:14.769
Mm.
Just one of the many reasons...

30:14.813 --> 30:18.468
- You need me.
- Oh, I need you, baby.

30:18.512 --> 30:22.081
I need you so much.

30:22.124 --> 30:24.126
Let him go, Richard.

30:24.170 --> 30:25.562
I wanna be alone with you.

30:25.606 --> 30:28.000
Yeah, that's all that I want.

30:28.043 --> 30:30.089
To be alone with you, my love.

30:30.132 --> 30:35.616
<i>♪</i>

30:35.659 --> 30:37.705
You guys
been here all night?

30:37.748 --> 30:41.013
We have programmed
virtually every shred

30:41.056 --> 30:43.624
of personal information
about Richard Wheatley

30:43.667 --> 30:45.321
into the rainbow table,

30:45.365 --> 30:48.934
and we still haven't
cracked the code.

30:48.977 --> 30:52.546
We tried birthdays, wedding
celebrations, bar mitsvahs--

30:52.589 --> 30:55.592
all the wonderful moments
people would commemorate.

31:03.600 --> 31:04.906
Oh, my God.

31:07.126 --> 31:08.388
Oh, my God.

31:08.431 --> 31:09.432
What--

31:09.476 --> 31:16.613
<i>♪</i>

31:18.180 --> 31:19.878
[keyboard clicking]

31:27.015 --> 31:28.147
Yes!

31:28.190 --> 31:29.583
We got it.

31:29.626 --> 31:30.801
You got it.

31:30.845 --> 31:32.542
Wait, what--what key
did you use?

31:33.848 --> 31:36.024
Um, the things
people want to commemorate.

31:36.068 --> 31:37.504
What did you plug in?

31:40.986 --> 31:43.336
I put in the date
that Kathy Stabler died.

31:43.379 --> 31:50.517
<i>♪</i>

32:02.877 --> 32:06.576
So everything's sweet?
You're in? Trusted?

32:06.620 --> 32:08.491
No one suspects anything?

32:10.145 --> 32:12.713
Still got that
Irish charm of yours.

32:14.802 --> 32:17.022
If things keep up like this,

32:17.065 --> 32:19.633
your boy Stabler's
gonna be my son-in-law.

32:19.676 --> 32:26.814
<i>♪</i>

32:45.093 --> 32:47.487
[elevator dings]

32:47.530 --> 32:48.531
[grunts]

32:48.575 --> 32:50.316
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:50.359 --> 32:51.926
This is an assault
on a private citizen.

32:51.970 --> 32:52.971
[grunts]

32:53.014 --> 32:54.537
I'll have your badge.

32:54.581 --> 32:56.496
You can have it.

32:56.539 --> 32:58.802
[whispers]
I had your wife.

32:58.846 --> 33:02.023
You--you got nothing.

33:02.067 --> 33:04.417
Where in the world
did I get these from then?

33:04.460 --> 33:05.635
[gasps]

33:07.898 --> 33:09.857
[both grunting]

33:09.900 --> 33:13.034
<i>♪</i>

33:13.078 --> 33:14.340
She couldn't wait
to take them off.

33:14.383 --> 33:16.124
Leave my life alone!

33:16.168 --> 33:18.953
[choking] I was
gonna take her to a hotel.

33:18.997 --> 33:21.912
But we wound up doing it
in the restaurant bathroom.

33:21.956 --> 33:28.571
<i>♪</i>

33:30.225 --> 33:33.141
Nobody touches my wife,
you Neanderthal.

33:33.185 --> 33:35.752
You hear?
You understand me?

33:35.796 --> 33:38.190
[both grunting]

33:38.233 --> 33:40.279
[screams]

33:40.322 --> 33:47.460
<i>♪</i>

33:53.118 --> 33:56.164
[phone ringing]

34:04.781 --> 34:06.218
Yeah?

34:06.261 --> 34:08.872
Rainbow table worked.
Anna's gonna give us a warrant

34:08.916 --> 34:10.222
to raid Wheatley's place.

34:10.265 --> 34:11.962
We just need
to figure out where it is.

34:12.006 --> 34:13.790
We don't need to.
I got him.

34:13.834 --> 34:14.922
<i>Where are you?</i>

34:14.965 --> 34:16.706
Doesn't matter. I got him.

34:16.750 --> 34:18.665
<i>Elliot, hear me.</i>

34:18.708 --> 34:20.971
We have a warrant
on his residence.

34:21.015 --> 34:22.538
Not on the man himself.

34:22.582 --> 34:24.105
- [coughs] <i>
- Let him go.</i>

34:24.149 --> 34:26.542
<i>Wherever the hell you are,</i> <i>
get out of there now.</i>

34:28.457 --> 34:32.200
- Where do you live? <i>
- Stabler? Stabler!</i>

34:32.244 --> 34:34.637
<i>Elliot, get out of there.</i>

34:36.857 --> 34:38.598
Inside your head.

34:38.641 --> 34:40.121
[grunts]

34:43.342 --> 34:44.821
[elevator dings]

34:44.865 --> 34:47.824
[laughing]

34:47.868 --> 34:54.744
<i>♪</i>

34:54.788 --> 34:57.269
Inside your head.

34:57.312 --> 35:00.489
[laughing]

35:16.375 --> 35:17.724
My office.

35:19.769 --> 35:21.206
That's not how it works,
Elliot.

35:21.249 --> 35:22.250
You know that.

35:22.294 --> 35:23.817
The date of my wife's murder.

35:23.860 --> 35:25.253
I know. I get it.

35:25.297 --> 35:27.473
But you are letting Wheatley
get the better of you.

35:27.516 --> 35:29.475
You know I saw him.

35:29.518 --> 35:31.172
He was standing there,
right next to McClane.

35:31.216 --> 35:33.131
That's not the issue.

35:33.174 --> 35:35.089
I know you're telling
the truth.

35:35.133 --> 35:37.135
But I can't lie to back you up.

35:37.178 --> 35:40.573
One of us
has got to be unimpeachable.

35:40.616 --> 35:42.314
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

35:42.357 --> 35:43.793
You're telling me
to stand down?

35:43.837 --> 35:45.099
For now.

35:45.143 --> 35:46.970
The Kosta Organization,
I never stood down.

35:47.014 --> 35:48.320
What did I give you?
Seven indictments.

35:48.363 --> 35:49.843
It's out of my hands.

35:49.886 --> 35:51.540
Brewster came to see me.

35:53.716 --> 35:55.631
Ayanna, please don't do this.

35:57.981 --> 35:59.722
I don't have a choice.

35:59.766 --> 36:02.812
<i>♪</i>

36:02.856 --> 36:06.033
This is exactly
what Wheatley wants.

36:06.076 --> 36:08.296
Okay, I'll take the psych eval.

36:08.340 --> 36:10.385
Just--you gotta buy me
some time.

36:10.429 --> 36:11.908
We have him.

36:14.520 --> 36:15.956
McClane. We have McClane.

36:19.394 --> 36:21.570
He called in.
He's asking for you.

36:23.181 --> 36:24.747
Sebastian McClane.

36:24.791 --> 36:25.792
<i>Where are you?</i>

36:25.835 --> 36:27.228
Never mind.

36:27.272 --> 36:29.012
I have a gift for you.

36:29.056 --> 36:30.797
<i>You have a gift for me?</i>

36:30.840 --> 36:33.452
Richard Wheatley
trussed up on a platter.

36:33.495 --> 36:35.236
You buyin' this?

36:35.280 --> 36:36.846
Do we have an option?

36:36.890 --> 36:40.110
I'm not quite sure
I know what that means.

36:40.154 --> 36:43.157
Are you saying that
you'll deliver Wheatley to me?

36:43.201 --> 36:45.028
Triangulating his call now.

36:45.072 --> 36:46.334
Every transaction I made,

36:46.378 --> 36:49.990
I left behind
a trail of digital dust.

36:50.033 --> 36:52.384
Random code, digital
fingerprints, signature.

36:52.427 --> 36:53.385
It's impossible to erase.

36:53.428 --> 36:57.911
<i>♪</i>

36:57.954 --> 36:59.739
That signature
will connect every transaction

36:59.782 --> 37:01.088
back to Wheatley.

37:01.131 --> 37:04.265
Proof he defrauded the market
for $700 million.

37:07.790 --> 37:10.358
What do you want in return?

37:10.402 --> 37:12.012
I got everything
I need at the moment.

37:12.055 --> 37:14.580
Are you prepared
to turn yourself in?

37:14.623 --> 37:15.711
Yeah, I know I said I would.

37:15.755 --> 37:18.584
But I'm having fun out here.

37:18.627 --> 37:21.804
People seem to like
what I'm doing.

37:21.848 --> 37:23.328
[bell dings]

37:24.981 --> 37:27.897
The call is being made from
the New York Public Library.

37:27.941 --> 37:29.334
Catch me if you can.

37:29.377 --> 37:31.423
But I advise you
to stay focused on Wheatley.

37:31.466 --> 37:32.293
<i>All right, well,</i> <i>
we'll do that.</i>

37:32.337 --> 37:34.121
Look, Sebastian.

37:34.164 --> 37:35.514
Sebastian.

37:35.557 --> 37:42.521
<i>♪</i>

37:57.057 --> 37:58.232
Detective Stabler.

37:58.276 --> 37:59.494
[grunts]

38:02.497 --> 38:07.241
How would you define the term
"obsessive" or "obsession?"

38:07.285 --> 38:09.461
Is that the word
they're using?

38:09.504 --> 38:10.984
I've done this before,
you know?

38:11.027 --> 38:11.941
I know.

38:13.421 --> 38:18.557
[sighs]
Obsession is an intense,

38:18.600 --> 38:21.690
some might say,
unhealthy preoccupation

38:21.734 --> 38:25.085
with a person or idea.

38:25.128 --> 38:26.956
Are you obsessed,
Detective Stabler?

38:29.089 --> 38:31.787
My wife used to tell me
I had OCD, but--

38:36.531 --> 38:38.881
You know the term,
"justice is blind?"

38:38.925 --> 38:39.795
Right?

38:39.839 --> 38:41.536
Which means it's impartial.

38:43.233 --> 38:45.105
It's not.

38:45.148 --> 38:47.020
It's blind.

38:47.063 --> 38:49.849
It can be easily led.

38:49.892 --> 38:54.854
Or manipulated
in the wrong direction.

38:54.897 --> 38:58.118
I am determined.

38:58.161 --> 38:59.511
Relentlessly determined.

39:00.903 --> 39:02.862
To guard
against that happening.

39:02.905 --> 39:04.864
Do you see injustice
happening right now?

39:04.907 --> 39:06.735
All the time,
everywhere, every day.

39:08.084 --> 39:12.306
It's my job
to make sure that...

39:12.350 --> 39:14.090
[sighs]
It doesn't happen.

39:15.918 --> 39:18.747
So you're
a warrior for justice?

39:20.793 --> 39:22.882
[phone ringing]
- Maybe in my younger days.

39:25.058 --> 39:26.189
I'm a guardian.

39:29.149 --> 39:30.585
[sighs]

39:35.590 --> 39:36.809
You're not Catholic, are you?

39:36.852 --> 39:39.594
[scoffs]
Muslim.

39:39.638 --> 39:42.423
But probably,
what you're about to say

39:42.467 --> 39:43.859
would apply
as well to my faith.

39:43.903 --> 39:46.645
I understand why you
or my superiors

39:46.688 --> 39:49.212
would be concerned
about my behavior.

39:49.256 --> 39:50.170
Regarding...

39:51.606 --> 39:53.913
My pursuit of this criminal.

39:55.480 --> 39:58.787
My obsession
in the pursuit of justice.

40:01.486 --> 40:04.924
When our faith
is taken seriously...

40:07.883 --> 40:09.798
It requires something of us.

40:12.584 --> 40:13.802
A call to duty.

40:17.502 --> 40:19.155
And I don't think we choose it.

40:19.199 --> 40:21.288
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

40:21.331 --> 40:22.768
It chooses us.

40:24.204 --> 40:26.859
Well, that brings me back
to my original question.

40:26.902 --> 40:30.689
This criminal you're pursuing,

40:30.732 --> 40:32.299
are you obsessed with him?

40:32.342 --> 40:37.957
<i>♪</i>

40:38.000 --> 40:42.309
If I tell you that the
criminal I'm pursuing,

40:42.352 --> 40:45.704
if not stopped, will take down
the New York Stock Exchange,

40:45.747 --> 40:48.533
and with it, the entire
global financial system...

40:51.013 --> 40:54.452
Am I delusional or obsessive?

40:54.495 --> 41:00.327
<i>♪</i>

41:00.370 --> 41:01.502
Give me two days
to prove that.

41:01.546 --> 41:02.851
And if I'm wrong,

41:02.895 --> 41:05.027
you won't have to ask
for my badge or my gun.

41:07.334 --> 41:09.031
I'll give them to you myself.

41:18.258 --> 41:21.174
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:21.217 --> 41:28.181
<i>♪</i>

41:48.288 --> 41:51.204
[wolf howls]
